&lt;p>The primary use of the Opener is to prepare your cooldown alignment for the rest of the encounter. With our new job design, it’s possible that we’ll actually have fight-specific openers down the stretch.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="standard-opener---no-pt">Standard Opener - No PT&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;div class="md__image">
 &lt;img id="[70 364 56 190 438 292]" src="https://github.com/RhyTamok/XIVdrg/blob/main/DRG/Graphics/Openers/Dragoon_Standard_Opener_-_No_PT.png?raw=true" onclick="openModal(this.id)" alt="Standard Opener - No PT" />
&lt;/div>

&lt;br>
We use our raidbuff Battle Litany after applying our DoT for party alignment, the rest of our buffs surround it with Geirskogul being used last to ensure its own potency is buffed by all our personal buffs and potential raidbuffs.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon Basic Guide</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/basic-guide/</link><pubDate>Mon, 09 Dec 2024 10:28:56 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/basic-guide/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="jobsmeleedragoonopenerjobsmeleedragoonopenersaving-the-dragoon">&lt;a href="https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/opener/">/jobs/melee/dragoon/opener/&lt;/a>Saving The Dragoon&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Dragoon is a relatively static melee DPS job with a high focus on weaving off-Global Cooldown (oGCD) actions between a rigid 10-hit sequence of Global Cooldown (GCD) actions. Burst windows can get hectic, and prioritizing the various skills you need to execute can become a rather significant hassle in some instances. Dawntrail has doubled down on this by introducing the ability to utilize even more oGCD actions at regular intervals, as if we didn’t have enough already.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon Leveling Guide</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/leveling-guide/</link><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 16:30:54 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/leveling-guide/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="dragoon-leveling-guide">Dragoon Leveling Guide&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="gear">Gear&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Always use the highest Item Level gear available to you. The increase of Strength and survivability outweighs potentially more favorable substats in lower Item Level gear. The total amount of substats is also higher.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Dragoons use Maiming armor and Slaying accessories.
Low level gear may not be labeled as such, so make sure you always equip gear that gives a bonus to Strength.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="know-your-role">Know Your Role&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Melee DPS jobs have a unique mechanic in Positionals. Certain actions will deal more damage when executed from the rear or flank of a target. Targets with continuous Target Rings will always take the increased damage from positional actions. &lt;br>
The Role Action True North allows you to disregard positional requirements for ten seconds per use. &lt;br>
A continuous target ring will always count positionals as successful, regardless of your position.

&lt;div class="md__image">
 &lt;img id="[139 116 5 68 148 137]" src="https://imgur.com/ANOqtwM.png" onclick="openModal(this.id)" alt="Positional zones" title="Positional zones" />
&lt;/div>
&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon FAQ</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/faq/</link><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jul 2024 11:18:50 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/faq/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Type &lt;code>!faq drg&lt;/code> in #bot_spam for a full list of commands to answer other common questions!&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>&lt;em>How does Raiden Thrust work?&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>Raiden Thrust is an upgraded True Thrust. It combos into both Disembowel and Vorpal Thrust and replaces True Thrust on your bar when it’s ready. You activate it by successfully landing the positional on the fifth hit of your combo (Fang and Claw or Wheeling Thrust following Wheeling Thrust or Fang and Claw, respectively). If you fail, you get to press True Thrust and hear a laugh track play in the background.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon Stat Priority</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/stat-priority/</link><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jul 2024 11:16:22 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/stat-priority/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Dragoon Advanced Guide</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/advanced-guide/</link><pubDate>Wed, 21 Sep 2022 20:41:44 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/advanced-guide/</guid><description>&lt;p>Due to the nature of the Dragoon job design, advanced content is included and covered within the &lt;a href="https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/basic-guide/">Basic Guide&lt;/a>. If you have further questions regarding DRG optimization, please feel free to ask in the Discord server.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>